<main>
  <h1>üåü Ninth Month of Pregnancy ‚Äî FINAL MONTH!</h1>
  <p><strong>Your body is preparing for labor and delivery. Stay calm, be prepared, and keep track of baby's movements.</strong></p>

  <!-- Baby Growth -->
  <div class="section baby-growth">
    <h2>üë∂ Baby Growth</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Baby weight: ~2.7 to 3.5 kg</li>
      <li>Baby length: 45‚Äì50 cm</li>
      <li>Lungs fully developed ‚Üí ready to breathe outside</li>
      <li>Baby gains fat for warmth</li>
      <li>Baby settles head-down (cephalic) position</li>
      <li>Strong movements: Rolling + stretching</li>
      <li>Brain development continues rapidly</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Mother's Body Changes -->
  <div class="section mother-body">
    <h2>ü§∞ Mother's Body Changes</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>More pelvic pressure & frequent urination</li>
      <li>Backache, leg cramps, difficulty sleeping</li>
      <li>Cervix softens & dilates</li>
      <li>False labor pains (Braxton Hicks)</li>
      <li>Pinkish mucus discharge ‚Äî "mucus plug"</li>
      <li>Breathing easier if baby drops down</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Foods to Eat -->
  <div class="section foods-eat">
    <h2>üçΩÔ∏è Foods to Eat</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Protein-rich: Egg, milk, curd, chicken/fish, pulses</li>
      <li>Iron & calcium: Spinach, ragi, dates, beetroot, almonds</li>
      <li>Hydration: 8‚Äì10 glasses water/day</li>
      <li>Small frequent meals to avoid acidity</li>
      <li>Fiber-rich foods ‚Üí avoid constipation during delivery</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Foods to Avoid -->
  <div class="section foods-avoid">
    <h2>üö´ Foods to Avoid</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Oily, spicy food ‚Äî triggers acidity & discomfort</li>
      <li>Too much salt ‚Äî swelling ‚Üë</li>
      <li>Junk/outside food ‚Äî risk of infection</li>
      <li>Limit sweets ‚Üí maintain baby weight</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Exercises -->
  <div class="section exercise">
    <h2>üßò‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è Exercises & Activity</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>30 minutes walking daily</li>
      <li>Pelvic floor exercises (Kegel)</li>
      <li>Squats & prenatal yoga if approved</li>
      <li>Practice breathing exercises</li>
      <li>‚õî Avoid: Long travel, Heavy work, Sleeping on back</li>
      <li>üìå Sleep on left side to improve baby's oxygen supply</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Required Tests -->
  <div class="section tests">
    <h2>üß™ Required Tests & Check-ups</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Weekly ANC Check-up</li>
      <li>Fetal Heart Rate Monitoring</li>
      <li>Blood Pressure & Weight check</li>
      <li>Growth Scan if needed</li>
      <li>Baby Position Check</li>
      <li>Urine Test (infection/protein)</li>
      <li>Non-Stress Test if reduced movements</li>
      <li>GBS test depends on hospital</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Warning Symptoms -->
  <div class="section warning">
    <h2>‚ö†Ô∏è Warning Symptoms</h2>
    <ul style="color:#c62828">
      <li>Severe abdominal pain / contractions every 5‚Äì10 mins</li>
      <li>Water breaking</li>
      <li>Bleeding</li>
      <li>Very less/no baby movements</li>
      <li>High fever, severe headache, swelling ‚Äî pre-eclampsia</li>
      <li>Convulsions, dizziness, blurred vision</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Hospital Bag -->
  <div class="section hospital-bag grid-2">
    <div>
      <h4 style="color:#4caf50; border-bottom:2px solid #4caf50; padding-bottom:6px;">For Mother</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Hospital records & ID</li>
        <li>Maternity gown & shawl</li>
        <li>Sanitary pads</li>
        <li>Comfortable clothes, slippers</li>
        <li>Toiletries</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h4 style="color:#4caf50; border-bottom:2px solid #4caf50; padding-bottom:6px;">For Baby</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Diapers, baby clothes, blanket, cap, socks</li>
        <li>Baby wipes, feeding essentials</li>
